            "title": "Due diligence and the business transaction : getting a deal done",
            "abstract": [
                "Intro -- Due Diligence and the Business Transaction -- Contents -- About the Author -- Preface -- Chapter 1: Introduction -- Due Diligence: Critical in a Business Transaction -- Chapter 2: What Is Due Diligence? -- Due Diligence Defined -- Due Diligence: A Fundamental Aspect of Most Business Transactions -- The Goal of Due Diligence: Understanding the Business Cornerstones -- Creating the Due Diligence Plan -- Chapter 3: The Due Diligence Questionnaire -- Due Diligence Questions: Standard Questions -- Topic 1: Basic Company Information -- Issue: The proper name of the entity (including any d/b/a names), the address of the business operation and assets, and the... -- Issue: Information about the company and the rights of equity owners as contained in the formation and governing documents ... -- Issue: The ownership structure of the business -- Topic 2: Ownership of Assets -- Issue: Ownership of key assets -- Issue: Ownership of intellectual property -- Topic 3: Financial/Tax Matters -- Issue: Financial status of the company as documented by company financial records -- Topic 4: Significant Agreements, Contracts, and Undertakings -- Issue: The company's material agreements or undertakings -- Issue: The financial and business terms of key customer agreements -- Issue: Supplier/vendor agreements -- Issue: Lease agreements -- Issue: Product, technology, or service license agreements -- Topic 5: Common Legal Questions -- Issue: Necessary licenses to conduct business -- Issue: Compliance with applicable laws -- Issue: Compliance with the company's governing documents -- Issue: Legal claims and proceedings -- Topic 6: Employees/Key Personnel -- Conclusion -- Chapter 4: Tailoring Due Diligence to the Transaction -- Due Diligence: Common Questions Based on Deal Type -- The Financing Transaction -- Common Financing Transaction Issues.",
                "Shows how to conduct effective due diligence investigations in a variety of business transactions, including the buying or selling of a business. For businesses ranging from small startups on up to billion-dollar companies. Provides useful guidelines and information for all parties involved in a transaction. Shows how to read, interpret, and respond to the information learned through a due diligence investigation regardless of the side of the transaction you are on. Provides solutions for addressing due diligence issues during the negotiation of the business transaction, drafting of the transactional documents, and the pre- and post-closing periods. Berkman is a prominent attorney specializing in all aspects of due diligence and has a popular blog at mybizlawyerblog.com. Berkman lectures often throughout the year and will push the book in these seminars as well as his social media outlets."
            ],
